X(STR_HELP_HELP,
  "Commands:\n"
  "HELP (command|rom)  - \aThis help or expanded help for command or rom.\n"
  "HELP ABOUT|SYSTEM   - \aAbout includes credits. System for general usage.\n"
  "STATUS              - \aShow status of system and connected devices.\n"
  "SET (attr) (value)  - \aChange or show settings.\n"
  "DIR (dir|drive)     - \aList contents of directory.\n"
  "LS (dir)            - \aChange or show current directory.\n"
  "(MSC)0:             - \aMSC0:-MSC9: Change current storage device.\n"
  "LOAD file           - \aLoad ROM file. Start if contains reset vector.\n"
  "INFO file           - \aShow help text, if any, contained in ROM file.\n"
  "INSTALL file (rom)  - \aInstall ROM file on RIA.\n"
  "rom                 - \aLoad and start an installed ROM.\n"
  "REMOVE rom          - \aRemove ROM from RIA.\n"
  "REBOOT              - \aReboot the RIA. Will load selected boot ROM.\n"
  "RESET               - \aStart 6502 at current reset vector ($FFFC).\n"
  "FLASH file          - \aFlash UF2 file to update RIA or VGA firmware.\n"
  "MKDIR dir           - \aMake a new directory.\n"
  "UNLINK file|dir     - \aDelete a file or empty directory.\n"
  "COPY src dst        - \aCopy a file.\n"
  "MOVE src dst        - \aMove or rename a file or directory.\n"
  "DISK sub drv ...    - \aInfo, label, format, erase, or verify a disk.\n"
  "UPLOAD file         - \aWrite file. Binary chunks follow.\n"
  "BINARY addr len crc - \aWrite memory. Binary data follows.\n"
  "0000 (00 00 ...)    - \aRead or write memory.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET,
  "Settings:\n"
  "HELP SET attr      - \aShow information about a setting.\n"
  "SET PHI2 (kHz)     - \aQuery or set PHI2 speed. This is the 6502 clock.\n"
  "SET BOOT (rom|-)   - \aSelect ROM to boot from cold start. \"-\" for none.\n"
  "SET TZ (tz)        - \aQuery or set time zone.\n"
  "SET KB (layouts)   - \aQuery or set keyboard layouts.\n"
  "SET CP (cp)        - \aQuery or set code page.\n"
  "SET VGA (0|1|2)    - \aQuery or set display type for VGA output.\n"
  "SET NFC (0|1|2|86) - \aDisable or enable NFC reader. 2 scans for PN532.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_W,
  "SET RF (0|1)       - \aDisable or enable radio.\n"
  "SET RFCC (cc|-)    - \aSet country code for RF devices. \"-\" for worldwide.\n"
  "SET SSID (ssid|-)  - \aSet SSID for WiFi. \"-\" for none.\n"
  "SET PASS (pass|-)  - \aSet password for WiFi. \"-\" for none.\n"
  "SET PORT (port)    - \aSet TCP port for remote console telnet access.\n"
  "SET KEY (key|-)    - \aSet passkey for remote console access. \"-\" for none.\n"
  "SET BLE (0|1|2|86) - \aDisable or enable Bluetooth LE. 2 enables pairing.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SYSTEM,
  "The Picocomputer does not use a traditional parallel ROM like a 27C64 or "
  "similar. Instead, this monitor is used to prepare the 6502 RAM with software "
  "that would normally be on a ROM chip. The 6502 is currently in-reset right "
  "now; the RESB line is low. What you are seeing is coming from the RP6502-RIA. "
  "You can return to this monitor at any time by pressing CTRL-ALT-DEL or sending "
  "a break to the serial port. Since these signals are handled by the RP6502-RIA, "
  "they will always stop the 6502, even when crashed. This monitor can do scripted "
  "things that are useful for developing software. It also provides interactive "
  "commands like typing a hex address to see the corresponding RAM value:\n"
  "]0200\n"
  "0200  DA DA DA DA DA DA DA DA  |........|\n"
  "The 64KB of extended memory (XRAM) is mapped from $10000 to $1FFFF. "
  "Request a range of memory with the \"-\" character:\n"
  "]10000-100FF\n"
  "You can also set memory. For example, to set the reset vector:\n"
  "]FFFC 00 02\n"
  "Intel HEX format is allowed:\n"
  "]:02FFFC00000201\n"
  "Manually manipulating memory is useful for some light debugging, but the real "
  "power is from the other commands you can explore with this help system.\n"
  "Have fun!\n")

X(STR_HELP_DIR,
  "LS (also aliased as DIR) and CD are used to navigate USB mass storage "
  "devices. You can change to a different USB device with 0: to 7:. Use the "
  "STATUS command to get a list of mounted drives.\n")

X(STR_HELP_MKDIR,
  "MKDIR is used to create new directories. Use UNLINK to remove empty directories.\n")

X(STR_HELP_LOAD,
  "LOAD and INFO read ROM files from a USB drive. A ROM file contains both "
  "ASCII information for the user and binary information for the system. "
  "Lines may end with either LF or CRLF. The first line must be:\n"
  "#!RP6502\n"
  "This is followed by HELP/INFO lines that begin with a # and a space:\n"
  "# Cool Game V0.0 by Awesome Dev\n"
  "After the info lines, binary data is prefixed with ASCII lines containing "
  "hex or decimal numbers indicating the address, length, and CRC-32.\n"
  "$C000 1024 0x0C0FFEE0\n"
  "This is followed by the binary data. The maximum length is 1024 bytes, so "
  "repeat as necessary. The CRC-32 is calculated using the same method as zip. "
  "If the ROM file contains data for the reset vector $FFFC-$FFFD then the "
  "6502 will be reset (started) immediately after loading.\n")

X(STR_HELP_INSTALL,
  "INSTALL and REMOVE manage the ROMs installed in the RP6502 RIA flash memory. "
  "ROM files must contain a reset vector to be installed. A list of installed "
  "ROMs is shown on the base HELP screen. Once installed, these ROMs become an "
  "integrated part of the system and can be loaded manually by simply using their "
  "name like any other command. The ROM name must not conflict with any other "
  "system command, must start with a letter, and may only contain up to 16 ASCII "
  "letters and numbers. If the file contains an extension, it must be \".rp6502\", "
  "which will be stripped upon install.\n")

X(STR_HELP_REBOOT,
  "REBOOT will restart the RP6502-RIA. It does the same thing as pressing a "
  "reboot button attached to the RIA RUN pin or interrupting the power supply.\n")

X(STR_HELP_RESET,
  "RESET will start the 6502 by bringing RESB high. This monitor will be "
  "suspended until the 6502 stops with a UART break, CTRL-ALT-DEL, or exit().\n")

X(STR_HELP_FLASH,
  "FLASH reads a UF2 file from a USB drive and flashes it to the RIA or VGA. "
  "If flashing fails, recover via USB using the standard BOOTSEL method (hold "
  "BOOTSEL while connecting USB to a computer then copy file).\n")

X(STR_HELP_UPLOAD,
  "UPLOAD is used to send a file from another system to the local filesystem. "
  "The file may be any type with any name and will overwrite an existing file "
  "of the same name. For example, you can send a ROM file along with other "
  "files containing graphics or level data for a game. Then you can LOAD the "
  "game and test it. The upload is initiated with a filename.\n"
  "]UPLOAD filename.bin\n"
  "The system will respond with a \"}\" prompt or an error message starting with "
  "a \"?\". Any error will abort the upload and return you to the monitor. "
  "There is no retry as this is not intended to be used on lossy connections. "
  "Specify each chunk with a length, up to 1024 bytes, and CRC-32 which you can "
  "compute from any zip library.\n"
  "}$400 $0C0FFEE0\n"
  "Send the binary data and you will get another \"}\" prompt or \"?\" error. "
  "The transfer is completed with the END command or a blank line. Your choice.\n"
  "}END\n"
  "You will return to a \"]\" prompt on success or \"?\" error on failure.\n")

X(STR_HELP_UNLINK,
  "UNLINK removes a file. Its intended use is for scripting on another system "
  "connected to the monitor. For example, you might want to delete save data "
  "as part of automated testing.\n")

X(STR_HELP_COPY,
  "COPY duplicates a file. The destination can be a new filename or a directory.\n")

X(STR_HELP_MOVE,
  "MOVE renames a file or directory or relocates it on the same drive. The "
  "destination can be a new name or a directory.\n")

X(STR_HELP_BINARY,
  "BINARY is the fastest way to get code or data from your build system to the "
  "6502 RAM. Use the command \"BINARY addr len crc\" with a maximum length of 1024 "
  "bytes and the CRC-32 calculated with a zip library. Then send the binary. "
  "You will return to a \"]\" prompt on success or \"?\" error on failure.\n")

X(STR_HELP_STATUS,
  "STATUS will show the status of all hardware in and connected to the RIA.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_PHI2,
  "PHI2 is the 6502 clock speed in kHz. The valid range is " STR_PHI2_MIN_MAX " but not all "
  "frequencies are available. In that case, the next highest frequency will "
  "be automatically calculated and selected. Setting is saved on the RIA flash.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_BOOT,
  "BOOT selects an installed ROM to be automatically loaded and started when the "
  "system is powered up or rebooted. For example, you might want the system to "
  "immediately boot into BASIC or an operating system CLI. Using \"-\" for the "
  "argument will have the system boot into the monitor you are using now. "
  "Setting is saved on the RIA flash.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_TZ,
  "You can set your time zone from the table below with just the city like "
  "\"SET TZ LOS_ANGELES\" or the full name \"SET TZ AMERICA/LOS_ANGELES\". "
  "Locations not in the table below can SET TZ to a POSIX TZ string with, for "
  "example, \"SET TZ PST8PDT,M3.2.0/2,M11.1.0/2\". The easiest way to get a "
  "POSIX TZ string is to ask an AI \"posix tz for {your location}\".\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_LOC,
  "SET LOC selects the display language. When SET CP is automatic it also sets "
  "the code page. e.g. SET LOC EN\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_KB,
  "SET KB selects keyboard layouts. You may specify multiple layouts which "
  "you can cycle between with Super+Space. e.g. SET KB US US-INTL\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_CP,
  "SET CP selects the system OEM code page. SET CP 0 is automatic (the default): "
  "the code page follows the locale set with SET LOC. Any other value is a fixed "
  "override. Supported: 437, 720, 737, 771, 775, 850, 852, 855, 857, 860, 861, "
  "862, 863, 864, 865, 866, 869.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_VGA,
  "SET VGA selects the display type for VGA output. All canvas resolutions are "
  "supported by all display types. Display type is used to maintain square "
  "pixels and minimize letterboxing. Note that 1280x1024 is 5:4 so 4:3 graphics "
  "will be letterboxed slightly but you'll get 2 extra rows on the terminal.\n"
  "  0 - \a640x480, for 4:3 displays\n"
  "  1 - \a640x480 and 1280x720, for 16:9 displays\n"
  "  2 - \a1280x1024, for 5:4 SXGA displays\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_NFC,
  "Setting 0 disables NFC reader. Setting 1 enables. Setting 2 scans all VCPs to "
  "find a PN532 device. Setting 86 clears the saved NFC device.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_RF,
  "SET RF (0|1) turns all radios off or on.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_RFCC,
  "Set this so the CYW43 can use the best radio frequencies for your country. "
  "Using \"-\" will clear the country code and default to a worldwide setting.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_SSID,
  "This is the Service Set Identifier for your WiFi network. Setting \"-\" will "
  "disable WiFi.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_PASS,
  "This is the password for your WiFi network. Use \"-\" to clear password.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_BLE,
  "Setting 0 disables Bluetooth LE. Setting 1 enables. Setting 2 enters pairing "
  "mode which will remain active until successful. Setting 86 clears all bonds "
  "and disconnects all devices.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_PORT,
  "SET PORT sets the TCP port for remote console access via telnet. The standard "
  "telnet port is 23. Setting 0 disables the telnet console. Both PORT and KEY "
  "must be set to enable.\n")

X(STR_HELP_SET_KEY,
  "SET KEY sets the passkey for remote console access. Use \"-\" to clear. "
  "Both PORT and KEY must be set to enable telnet console access.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK,
  "Disk:\n"
  "HELP DISK sub        - \aShow help for a disk subcommand.\n"
  "DISK INFO drv        - \aShow device, format, and usage.\n"
  "DISK LABEL drv (lbl) - \aShow or set the volume label.\n"
  "DISK FORMAT drv ..   - \aCreate a filesystem. See HELP DISK FORMAT.\n"
  "DISK ERASE drv       - \aOverwrite all data with zeros. See HELP DISK ERASE.\n"
  "DISK VERIFY drv      - \aRead every sector and report bad ones.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK_INFO,
  "DISK INFO drive\n"
  "Shows the device, the on-disk format (scheme, filesystem, cluster size, "
  "label), and how full the volume is. Drives are named MSCn: or n:.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK_FORMAT,
  "DISK FORMAT drive [/fat|/exfat] [/sfd|/mbr|/gpt] [/512|/4k...] [/quick|/full] [label]\n"
  "Creates a filesystem on a drive named MSCn: or n:. /fat (default) is most "
  "compatible; /exfat suits large drives. Layout: /sfd, /mbr, or /gpt; default "
  "is SFD for floppies, MBR for flash. /512 through larger powers of two set the "
  "cluster size (default by capacity). "
  "/quick (default) writes only the filesystem; /full adds a low-level format "
  "(floppies only). A preview is shown; type YES to confirm.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK_FORMAT_BASIC,
  "DISK FORMAT drive [/sfd|/mbr] [/512|/4k...] [/quick|/full] [label]\n"
  "Creates a FAT filesystem on a drive named MSCn: or n:. Layout: /sfd or /mbr; "
  "default is SFD for floppies, MBR for flash. /512 through larger powers of two "
  "set the cluster size (default by "
  "capacity). /quick (default) writes only the filesystem; /full adds a "
  "low-level format (floppies only). A preview is shown; type YES to confirm.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK_ERASE,
  "DISK ERASE drive\n"
  "Destroys all data on a drive named MSCn: or n: by overwriting every sector "
  "with zeros, which defeats file-recovery software but may leave data in "
  "remapped flash cells. Type YES to confirm.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK_VERIFY,
  "DISK VERIFY drive\n"
  "Reads every sector of a drive named MSCn: or n: and reports any that fail. "
  "Read-only. Press Ctrl-C to stop.\n")

X(STR_HELP_DISK_LABEL,
  "DISK LABEL drive [label]\n"
  "With no label, shows the volume label of a drive named MSCn: or n:. With a "
  "label, sets it and prints the old and new names. Pass an empty \"\" to clear "
  "the label.\n")

XEND()
#undef XSUFFIX
